1. Abstract class allows both static and non-static members inside it
2. While providing the implementations for the methods you must have to either retain the vissibility or you need to increase it, but you cant dicrease it 
ex. A Default method cant be overiden as the private, it can be overriden as public or protected
3. Abstract class can't be final 
4. Abstract and static will never exists together, abstract method can't be static and vice versa
5. Abstract class cant be instantiated, but